{"word":"H7034 - קָלָה - qâlâh - kaw-law' - Base","slug":"H7034","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qâlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Base"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05DC;&#x05D4; - qa&#x0302;la&#x0302;h</b> - <i>kaw-law'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be light</i> (as implied in <i>rapid</i> motion), but figuratively only (<i>be</i> (causatively <i>hold</i>) <i>in contempt</i>): - base, contemn, despise, lightly esteem, set light, seem vile."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7036\">H7036</a>, <a href=\"#/H7037\">H7037</a>"}]}